5. RIGHT DRAWER / HAMBURGER DRAWER
====================================================

Replace the permanently crowded right panel with a pull-in / pull-out right drawer.

Purpose:
The right drawer holds secondary insight cards so the main dashboard has breathing room.

Add a hamburger / insight drawer button near the top-right:
- Icon: ☰ or ≡
- Label optional: Insights
- Position: top-right of main content near filters/status

Drawer behavior:
- Default can be open on desktop, collapsed on smaller screens.
- User can open/close the drawer.
- Store state in st.session_state["sales_drawer_open"].
- If using JS for smoother animation, use st.components.v1.html or CSS transitions.
- If JS becomes difficult, use Streamlit button to toggle drawer state.

Drawer CSS:
.right-drawer {
  position: fixed or sticky;
  right: 18px;
  top: 110px;
  width: 320px;
  max-width: 340px;
  height: calc(100vh - 140px);
  background: rgba(8, 22, 28, 0.94);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
  border-radius: 22px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
  backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
  transition: transform 0.25s ease, opacity 0.25s ease;
  z-index: 50;
}

.right-drawer.closed {
  transform: translateX(110%);
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.right-drawer.open {
  transform: translateX(0);
  opacity: 1;
}

